tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased HbA1c, which may reflect recent hypoglycemia or altered red cell turnover, and a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, possibly indicating increased platelet size variability (e.g., reactive or regenerative changes). No evidence of anemia, renal dysfunction, or electrolyte imbalance. Clinical correlation is recommended.
